  "report_name": "<filename without .pdf>",
  "report_title": "<full report title>",
  "emissions": {
    "scope_1": {
      "<year>": [
        {
          "value": <number>,
          "unit": "<string>",
          "label": "<string>"
        }
      ]
    },
    "scope_2_location_based": {
      "<year>": [
        {
          "value": <number>,
          "unit": "<string>",
          "label": "<string>"
        }
      ]
    },
    "scope_2_market_based": {
      "<year>": [
        {
          "value": <number>,
          "unit": "<string>",
          "label": "<string>"
        }
      ]
    },
    "scope_3": {
      "<year>": [
        {
          "value": <number>,
          "unit": "<string>",
          "label": "<string>"
        }
      ]
    }
  }
}
```

**Additional rules**
- Do **not** output years for which no total value is found.
- Do **not** output multiple entries for the same year unless the source provides distinct labelled totals (e.g., “Scope 2 (location‑based) – Total” and “Scope 2 (location‑based) – Purchased electricity”). In that case include each as a separate object in the array.
- Do **not** add any commentary, explanations, or extra whitespace outside the JSON object.
- If the report name or title cannot be determined, use an empty string `""` for the respective field.

